                    "endOffset": 163464,
                    "startOffset": 163461
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In [6] (with Jerrum) and [7] we considered the switch Markov chain on perfect matchings in bipartite and nonbipartite graphs.",
            "startOffset": 163436,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 222069,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec9",
            "sentence": "We gave a complete answer to the ergodicity question, and showed rapid mixing for the new class of quasimonotone graphs.",
            "startOffset": 221949,
            "title": "Conclusion and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 164795,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In this class the bipartite graph given by the cut between any bipartition of the vertices of the graph must be a monotone graph.",
            "startOffset": 164666,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 208116,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec6",
                    "title": "Flawless graphs without long holes"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec6.1",
            "sentence": "Note that pre-holes with fewer than 12 vertices may contain an interior triangle.",
            "startOffset": 208035,
            "title": "Minimal pre-holes in hole-free graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 168433,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec1",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec1.2",
            "sentence": "Again we start with some technical lemmas showing that the long hole enforces an annular structure in the absence of flaws.",
            "startOffset": 168310,
            "title": "Structure of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 183141,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec3.2",
            "sentence": "The following is similar to Lemma 5, but the details of the proof are slightly different.",
            "startOffset": 183052,
            "title": "Properties of flawless graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 163776,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "We considered the ergodicity and mixing properties of the chain.",
            "startOffset": 163712,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 175562,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec3.1",
            "sentence": "A bipartite graph is monotone if and only if the rows and columns of its biadjacency matrix can be permuted such that the ones appear consecutively and the boundaries of these intervals are monotonic functions of the row or column index.",
            "startOffset": 175325,
            "title": "Flaws and pre-holes"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 164414,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b10": {
                    "endOffset": 164399,
                    "startOffset": 164395
                },
                "b15": {
                    "endOffset": 164314,
                    "startOffset": 164310
                },
                "b4": {
                    "endOffset": 164413,
                    "startOffset": 164410
                },
                "b6": {
                    "endOffset": 164219,
                    "startOffset": 164216
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "We also showed in [6] that this class is, in fact, identical to the known class of bipartite permutation graphs [15], which is itself known to be identical to the class of proper interval bigraphs [10], see also [4].",
            "startOffset": 164198,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 169274,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec1",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec1.2",
