            "title": "Flaws and pre-holes"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 214534,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec6",
                    "title": "Flawless graphs without long holes"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec6.2",
            "sentence": "It remains to consider pre-holes in graphs which contain 5-holes, and may also contain triangles.",
            "startOffset": 214437,
            "title": "Preholes containing 5-holes and triangles"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 168252,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec1",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec1.2",
            "sentence": "The remaining forbidden subgraphs are pre-holes, also defined in 3.1.",
            "startOffset": 168183,
            "title": "Structure of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 222180,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec9",
            "sentence": "This led us to introduce a new \u201cquasi-\u201d operator on bipartite graph classes, which is of independent interest.",
            "startOffset": 222070,
            "title": "Conclusion and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 164129,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "The biadjacency matrices of graphs in the class have a \u201cstaircase\u201d structure.",
            "startOffset": 164052,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 164928,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In fact, \u201cquasi-\u201d is an operator on bipartite graph classes, and can be applied more generally.",
            "startOffset": 164833,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 167691,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec1",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec1.2",
            "sentence": "In Section 2.1 we give some examples.",
            "startOffset": 167654,
            "title": "Structure of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 164051,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b5": {
                    "endOffset": 163990,
                    "startOffset": 163987
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "This class of bipartite graphs was defined by Diaconis, Graham and Holmes in [5], motivated by statistical applications of perfect matchings.",
            "startOffset": 163910,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 176144,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b10": {
                    "endOffset": 176143,
                    "startOffset": 176139
                },
                "b15": {
                    "endOffset": 176109,
                    "startOffset": 176105
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec3.1",
            "sentence": "Monotone graphs are also called bipartite permutation graphs [15] and proper interval bigraphs [10].",
            "startOffset": 176044,
            "title": "Flaws and pre-holes"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 175644,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec3.1",
            "sentence": "That is, all the ones are in a staircase-shaped region in the biadjacency matrix.",
            "startOffset": 175563,
            "title": "Flaws and pre-holes"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 168556,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec1",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec1.2",
            "sentence": "Possible pre-holes must wind round this annulus once or twice.",
            "startOffset": 168494,
            "title": "Structure of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 208210,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec6",
                    "title": "Flawless graphs without long holes"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec6.1",
            "sentence": "However, the bound 12 is probably far from tight.",
            "startOffset": 208161,
            "title": "Minimal pre-holes in hole-free graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 217504,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec8",
            "sentence": "The recognition algorithm finds a pre-hole in a flawless graph, if there is one.",
            "startOffset": 217424,
            "title": "Recognising a pre-hole"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 175752,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "refoffsets": {
