                },
                "b2": {
                    "endOffset": 175720,
                    "startOffset": 175717
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec3.1",
            "sentence": "Equivalent characterisations exist, see [12] (Lemma 1.46 on page 52) or [2] (Proposition 6.2.1 on page 93):",
            "startOffset": 175645,
            "title": "Flaws and pre-holes"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 163909,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b6": {
                    "endOffset": 163807,
                    "startOffset": 163804
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In particular, we proved in [6] that the chain is rapidly mixing (i.e. converges in polynomial time) on the class of monotone graphs.",
            "startOffset": 163776,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 183854,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec3.2",
            "sentence": "See Fig. 11.",
            "startOffset": 183842,
            "title": "Properties of flawless graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 221948,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b7": {
                    "endOffset": 221842,
                    "startOffset": 221839
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec9",
            "sentence": "In [7] we considered the problem of ergodicity and rapid mixing of the switch chain in hereditary graph classes.",
            "startOffset": 221836,
            "title": "Conclusion and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 216003,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec7",
            "sentence": "Algorithm ??",
            "startOffset": 215991,
            "title": "Recognition algorithm"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 165054,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec1",
            "sentence": "In this view, quasimonotone graphs are quasi-monotone graphs, as formally defined in Section 2, and discussed in Section 2.1.",
            "startOffset": 164929,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 217723,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec8",
            "sentence": "This is exactly the recognition problem for the class ODDCHORDAL.",
            "startOffset": 217658,
            "title": "Recognising a pre-hole"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 216031,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec7",
            "sentence": "is a summary as pseudocode.",
            "startOffset": 216004,
            "title": "Recognition algorithm"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 183841,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec3",
                    "title": "The structure of quasimonotone graphs"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec3.2",
            "sentence": "The degree bound of Lemma 6 is tight.",
            "startOffset": 183804,
            "title": "Properties of flawless graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 217657,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "sec8",
            "sentence": "Therefore it is quite natural to ask whether we can find a pre-hole in any graph in polynomial time.",
            "startOffset": 217557,
            "title": "Recognising a pre-hole"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 212142,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "sec6",
                    "title": "Flawless graphs without long holes"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "sec6.1",
            "sentence": "Follows directly from Lemmas 6 and 22.",
            "startOffset": 212104,
            "title": "Minimal pre-holes in hole-free graphs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 197922,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b11": {
                    "endOffset": 197921,
                    "startOffset": 197915
                },
                "b9": {
                    "endOffset": 197921,
                    "startOffset": 197915
                }
            },
            "secId": "sec5",
            "sentence": "We will call these M\u00f6bius pre-holes, since we will show that such a pre-hole must be a M\u00f6bius ladder [9,11].",
